# Cline Rules for vx

## Project

vx is a universal development tool manager (Rust, 105 providers, Starlark DSL).
Users prefix commands with `vx` and tools auto-install on first use.

## Rules

1. Always use `vx` prefix for tool commands: `vx npm install`, `vx cargo build`
2. Never suggest manual tool installation — vx handles it
3. Terminology: Runtime (not Tool), Provider (not Plugin), provider.star (not provider config)
4. Tests go in `crates/<name>/tests/` — never `#[cfg(test)]` inline
5. Use `rstest` for parameterized tests
6. Logging: `tracing::info!`, `tracing::debug!` — never `println!`
7. Error handling: `anyhow::Result` (app), `thiserror` (lib)
8. Layer deps go downward only: CLI → Orchestration → Service → Foundation → Providers
9. New providers: Starlark DSL only (`provider.star`), no Rust code needed
10. Pre-commit: `vx just quick` (format → lint → test → build)
11. Commits: Conventional Commits format (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, etc.)
12. File size: Keep under 500 lines

